From: Disyer <daniel@tohka.us>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 14:03:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add SameSite cookie env var for cross-origin iframe

Add OVERLEAF_SAME_SITE_COOKIE env var to control the SameSite attribute
of the session cookie. Setting this to 'none' (with OVERLEAF_SECURE_COOKIE=true)
allows the Overleaf editor to be embedded in a cross-origin iframe
(e.g. QualiCheck) without the browser blocking the session cookie.

diff --git a/server-ce/config/settings.js b/server-ce/config/settings.js
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/server-ce/config/settings.js
+++ b/server-ce/config/settings.js
@@ -241,6 +241,9 @@ const settings = {
   // cookie with a secure flag (recommended).
   secureCookie: process.env.OVERLEAF_SECURE_COOKIE != null,

+  // 'SameSite' cookie setting for cross-origin iframe support.
+  sameSiteCookie: process.env.OVERLEAF_SAME_SITE_COOKIE || 'lax',
+
   // If you are running Overleaf Community Edition behind a proxy (like Apache, Nginx, etc)
   // then set this to true to allow it to correctly detect the forwarded IP
   // address and http/https protocol information.
